\par }\pard\plain \qj\fi576\sb240\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs22\cgrid {Qualified language (particularly the word }{\i may)}{ has been used in a number of places, generally where the author intended permissible simplifications. In each case, the qualification is that if the so-called simplification actually turns into a complication (for example because it makes the adoption of a standard existing component, such as a parser, more difficult) then that "simplification"}{\i  }{should be dropped like first-year, spaghetti code.
